net.proteusframework.processes.form.ui

Class FormControllerConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.processes.form.ui.FormControllerConfig

  • public class FormControllerConfig
extends Object
    Runtime configuration for showing a form process. If you set the FormProcess optional property, the UI will edit the existing FormProcess; otherwise, it will create a new FormProcess. You may also control which view will be displayed. Do not modify this config after it has been passed to the form API, e.g. through FormEntryComponent.
    Author:
    Jonathan Crosmer (jcrosmer@i2rd.com)

      • setCapacityListMap

        public FormControllerConfig setCapacityListMap(Map<com.i2rd.capacity.CapacityList,com.i2rd.capacity.CapacityList> capacityListMap)

        INTERNAL USE

        Set the map used to replace CapacityLists in the form. Each key should be a template list, and the value should be a linked clone of the key. When using the Capacity API, any references to a template list in the form definition will be replaced by the given value. See the Capacity API for more details on this feature. Defaults to empty map.
        Parameters:
        capacityListMap - the capacityListMap.
        Returns:
        this

      • setForcePermanentOnSubmit

        public void setForcePermanentOnSubmit(boolean forcePermanentOnSubmit)
        Set whether capacity reservations should be made permanent when the form is submitted. If false, the reservations will remain provisional even after submitting the form, and application code will have to make them permanent using FormProcessor.setChoicesAndReserveCapacity(ChoiceExtraValue, List, String, boolean, boolean, CapacityList) Defaults to true.
        Parameters:
        forcePermanentOnSubmit - true to make reservations permanent on submit
